==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paschal
<hw>Pas"chal</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧s"k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>paschalis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pascal</ets>. See
<er>Pasch</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the passover, or to
Easter; <as>as, a <ex>paschal</ex> lamb; <ex>paschal</ex>
eggs.</as></def> <rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Paschal candle</b></col> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>, <cd>a
large wax candle, blessed and placed on the altar on Holy Saturday, or
the day before Easter.</cd> -- <col><b>Paschal flower</b></col>. See
<cref>Pasque flower</cref>, under <er>Pasque</er>.</cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1048 --></p>

